const faqs = [
  {
    q: "My dryer hums but the drum won't turn. What's wrong?",
    a: "The two most likely causes are a broken drive belt (most common, year 5 to 10 typical) or a seized drum roller (year 7 to 12). A broken belt produces a quiet hum or no sound at all when you press start. A seized drum roller produces a loud thumping or grinding sound. We test both at the diagnostic visit by manually rotating the drum: free movement points to belt, resistance points to rollers."
  },
  {
    q: "I hear a thumping sound and the drum barely turns. What is that?",
    a: "Worn drum rollers, almost always. Most dryers have two or four rollers (small wheels) that support the rear or front of the drum. When the bearings wear out, the rollers seize or develop flat spots, which causes the thumping. Replace all rollers as a set, not just the failed one, because the others are typically a few months from failing too. Roller kits run $145 to $245 installed."
  },
  {
    q: "Can I replace the dryer belt myself?",
    a: "Mechanically yes for handy homeowners, but the belt itself is the cheapest part of the repair. The reason belts break early is usually a worn idler pulley or a degraded drum roller, both of which need to be inspected and often replaced at the same time. We replace belt plus idler pulley together as a standard procedure, because replacing the belt alone on a year 8 dryer typically gets you a callback in 6 to 12 months."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between belt failure and motor failure?",
    a: "Belt failure: motor runs (you hear it humming), drum doesn't turn, drum spins freely by hand. Motor failure: motor doesn't run at all (silent or clicks once and stops), drum may or may not turn freely by hand. Motor failures are much rarer (year 12+ typical) and almost always come with a burnt-electronics smell. We test motor windings with a multimeter to confirm before quoting a motor replacement."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the typical cost?",
    a: "Belt plus idler pulley replacement (most common no-tumble repair): $185 to $325 depending on brand and access. Drum roller kit: $145 to $245. Drive motor replacement: $345 to $525 (parts cost varies by brand). Drum bearing or rear seal: $245 to $385. Multi-component repair on a year 10+ unit: $385 to $525. The $89 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair."
  },
  {
    q: "When should I replace the dryer instead of repairing the drum drive?",
    a: "Mid-tier dryer (under $700 retail) at year 12+ with motor failure or drum bearing failure: replacement is often the right call. Belt or roller failures alone almost always favor repair regardless of age because the labor is short and parts are inexpensive. Premium tier (Miele, Bosch, LG WashTower, Samsung Bespoke): repair through year 12 makes sense even for motor failures."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "Ninety days SDAR labor and parts warranty on the work we perform. If the same component fails within 90 days, we replace it free. BHGS #A49573 and BBB A+ accredited. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410."
  }
];

